Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of practical exercises in MOOCs that teach programming skills, which falls under the category of computer science education (cs.CE). The paper also analyzes data from over 3 million executions and scoring runs of participants' task submissions, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and could be categorized under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the difficulty of tasks and the patterns in which students approach them, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) or software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes approaches and methods to improve programming courses, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY).
